This paper deals with privacy-preserving data analysis, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on range queries, which are commonly used in database systems (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper addresses privacy concerns, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). The methods proposed in the paper involve statistical analysis, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves the use of data structures to efficiently process range queries, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
